  "text": "Experiments were performed on adult (3-4 months old) male Rhcg +/+ , Rhcg +/2 and Rhcg 2/2 CD1 mice [CITATION_1] . ''One spot'' urines were collected after a fasting of 16 hours with water ad libitum. Ammonium concentrations in the urine samples were measured by L-glutamate deshydrogenase determination. Ammonium concentrations are reported to urinary creatinine levels. The creatininuria was assayed with the CR01 kit (Oxford Biomedical Research).",
